ultiple personalities. I've been searching on the net, and I have come up with some information on this disorder. The problem is that they don't really answer any of my questions. Maybe someone could help me with this?<br>
<br>
Theoretically, would it be possible for one entity to be in conflict with the other? If the person in question is in a coma-like state, would it be possible for the subconscious part of the mind to create a place where one entity and another entity would have the ability to interact with each other within the limits of the person's mind? Would it be possible, if the person was fully conscious, for one entity to indirectly communicate with the other?<br>
<br>
Yeah, that second one gave me a headache and I'm still ot sure if I really understand it.<br>
<br>
This is all in theory, and I guess it doesn't have to be completely accurate since its for a mange that will proabably never be seen by the public. At any rate, what do you think? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uwomble38.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Womble38</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/29/02 1:42:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Multiple Personalities</span><hr size=1> Ok I'm no expert on this, but if I recall, it is possible for one person to have two completely separate personalities, which have no awareness of each other. I believe the technical term is compartmentalisation, whereby the personality and memory centres of the brain are partitioned. A bit like a hard drive with two different formats i.e. it's the same brain but one half doesn't know the other half is there, nor can it access the other half. This results in a one personality, for example the normal one not remembering any of the actions of the psychotic killer half of themselves (corny I know), in most cases it's just like going to sleep and when you wake you're laying in bed with a blood stained knife not knowing how it got there.<br>
<br>
Hope this is of some help - W38 -<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=keokekin>Keoke Kin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/30/02 2:17:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Multiple Personalities</span><hr size=1> Heheh, psychotic killer. That's actually close to his other half, which is more of the 'perfect soldier' whom neither questions orders nor hesitates in following them. The original half is very childish, though no one is really sure which one is the original half.<br>
Compartmentalism? Yeah, that makes sense now that I think about how I implement them. In any case, I could just blame the etheric plane and symbiote for anything that seems weird.<br>
<br>
Some Info on the manga and character might help.<br>
The manga itself is set around 10-50 thousand years into the future, where Earth is destroyed and people are liviing happily in the Draconis solar system, spread among three different planets each with a habitable atmosphere. Each planet actually has quite a long history, but I'll make it brief. Each one developed independantly of the others, and so the cultres, technological advancement, etc. vary greatly.<br>
The first was practically a paradise, being remarkably similar to Earth, except this planet had slightly more land then water.<br>
The second was a planet with very hostile weather conditions, forcing the colonists to adapt and practically capitalize on eficiency. This made them the most technologically advanced out of the three.<br>
The third was almost pure land, made mostly of desserts and mountains. People here are very careful. Everything that moves is considered deadly, and some of the dead things still move.<br>
People generally live to be 3-5 hundred years, and there is a required 50 years of schooling.<br>
Now for the character.<br>
His name's Keoke (I pronounce it 'kay-oh-ki', but it could also be pronounced as strict japanese 'kay-oh-kay' He prefers the first one, though.) He's actually an artificially created half-wolf and a prototype for future soldiers. He was created through genetic engineering, almost entirely from scratch, to have the ability to become a half-fighter/half-wizard.<br>
He is biologically in his early teens, but his actual age is closer to his mid 30s-40s. He generally has messy hair which reaches just above his shoulders. Standing at about 5'3'', complete with really light blue (almost white) eyes, though that would be hard to prove since his hair is almost always covering most of his eyes. (He's drawn as cat-bow)<br>
<br>
Hope that wasn't too long. Thanks! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=keokekin>Keoke Kin</A> at: 5/30/02 2:18:24 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uascendedbob.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ascended Bob</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/30/02 2:38:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Multiple Personalities</span><hr size=1> Well this is fiction man. Anything is possible. The personality thing has been done sometimes just like what you speak of. I'm not saying its un-original or anything like that because it is pretty original sounding. I just think you can get away with making it up if its not possible. So don't even worry about it. In fact the etheric plane and symbiote things sound less feasable than the original idea. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=keokekin>Keoke Kin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/31/02 3:02:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=648.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmm</span><hr size=1> Well, I guess you're right.<br>
I guess it really doesn't matter in fiction.<br>
In any case, thanks for the advice.<br>
